ension of sharing, not as a sharing of things that we can contain and own, but as a process that divides us up and shares us out in community with one another. This book traces this problem through a wide array of fields ranging from biopolitics, communitarianism, existentialism, phenomenology, political economy, radical philosophy, and social theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunitiesxPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Social Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846187840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438461878423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438461878/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles